<h4 id="personalize-the-abstract-page">Personalize the abstract page.</h4>

<!--more-->

<p>The  new PubMed has been around for sometime. It looks much better both on the desktop and on mobile browser. That is, compared with its old version. Some of the lethal design faults includeâ€¦</p>

<ul>
  <li>fonts too damn small</li>
  <li>header too damn big</li>
  <li>too many useless stuff</li>
  <li>subtle color change for visited links</li>
  <li>NO IMPACT FACTOR !!!</li>
</ul>

<p>Using the chrome plug-in stylish and some rudimentary css knowledge, I have redesign the display. Change the fonts and make them bigger, hide all unnecessary contents, highlight the journal name and IF. For example:</p>

<div class="language-css highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nc">.docsum-title</span><span class="nd">:visited</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="nl">color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#0000bc</span> <span class="cp">!important</span> <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="c">/* make visited links appear in a specific color */</span>

<span class="nc">.ncbi-header</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="nl">display</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">none</span> <span class="cp">!important</span> <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="c">/* hide the NCBI header */</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
